---
import Base from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---
<Base title="Support Orbital Temple - Join the Mission">

  <main class="artwork-page">

    <!-- Main Title -->
    <h1 class="artwork-title">
      Support Orbital Temple
    </h1>

    <!-- Opening Vision -->
    <p class="artwork-text" style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto 3rem auto;">
      On <strong>November 28, 2025</strong>, the first purely artistic satellite from the Global South will launch from <strong>India</strong> aboard an <strong>ISRO</strong> rocket. <strong>Orbital Temple</strong> is a monument to radical inclusion, a platform for education, and a catalyst for global conversation about the future of the sacred in the age of space exploration.
    </p>

    <!-- Visual Content Section -->
    <figure style="margin: 3rem auto 48px auto; max-width: 900px;">
      <div id="video-container" style="position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden; border-radius: 4px; cursor: pointer;">
        <!-- Video Thumbnail -->
        <img
          id="video-thumbnail"
          src="https://img.youtube.com/vi/xf-Fj_YaRik/maxresdefault.jpg"
          alt="Orbital Temple video introduction"
          style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; border-radius: 4px;"
        />
        <!-- Play Button Overlay -->
        <div id="play-button" style="position: absolute; top: 50%; left: 50%; transform: translate(-50%, -50%); width: 80px; height: 80px; background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7); border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; transition: all 0.3s ease;">
          <svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="white" style="margin-left: 4px;">
            <path d="M8 5v14l11-7z"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <!-- YouTube iframe (hidden initially) -->
        <iframe
          id="youtube-iframe"
          style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border-radius: 4px; display: none;"
          src=""
          title="Orbital Temple video introduction"
          frameborder="0"
          allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
          allowfullscreen>
        </iframe>
      </div>
      <figcaption style="font-size: var(--text-body-sm); line-height: var(--text-body-sm-lh); color: var(--color-ot-light); opacity: 0.6; margin-top: 8px; text-align: right;">
        Orbital Temple video introduction, 1 min.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <script>
      // Click-to-play functionality
      const videoContainer = document.getElementById('video-container');
      const videoThumbnail = document.getElementById('video-thumbnail');
      const playButton = document.getElementById('play-button');
      const youtubeIframe = document.getElementById('youtube-iframe');

      videoContainer?.addEventListener('click', function() {
        // Hide thumbnail and play button
        if (videoThumbnail) videoThumbnail.style.display = 'none';
        if (playButton) playButton.style.display = 'none';

        // Show and load YouTube video with autoplay
        if (youtubeIframe) {
          youtubeIframe.src = 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/xf-Fj_YaRik?start=14&autoplay=1';
          youtubeIframe.style.display = 'block';
        }

        // Remove cursor pointer after video loads
        videoContainer.style.cursor = 'default';
      });

      // Hover effect on play button
      videoContainer?.addEventListener('mouseenter', function() {
        if (playButton && playButton.style.display !== 'none') {
          playButton.style.transform = 'translate(-50%, -50%) scale(1.1)';
          playButton.style.background = 'rgba(250, 212, 58, 0.9)';
        }
      });

      videoContainer?.addEventListener('mouseleave', function() {
        if (playButton && playButton.style.display !== 'none') {
          playButton.style.transform = 'translate(-50%, -50%) scale(1)';
          playButton.style.background = 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7)';
        }
      });
    </script>

    <!-- What We've Accomplished -->
    <h2 class="artwork-subtitle">
      What We've Accomplished
    </h2>

    <p class="artwork-text artwork-text--section-end">
      After years of research and development, the mission is ready. We have completed <strong>hardware and software development</strong> for the satellite, passed <strong>official shaker tests</strong> required for flight certification, and finalized our contract with ISRO. The satellite is built. The technology works. We are cleared for launch.
    </p>

    <!-- Funding Progress -->
    <h2 class="artwork-subtitle">
      Funding Progress
    </h2>

    <div style="max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto 3rem auto; padding: 2rem; background: rgba(250, 212, 58, 0.03); border: 1px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); border-radius: 4px;">

      <p class="artwork-text" style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        <strong style="font-size: 22px; color: var(--color-ot-gold200);">$29,000</strong> raised of <strong style="font-size: 22px;">$249,000</strong> goal
      </p>

      <!-- Progress Bar -->
      <div style="width: 100%; height: 8px; background: rgba(250, 212, 58, 0.1); border-radius: 4px; overflow: hidden; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        <div style="width: 11.65%; height: 100%; background: var(--color-ot-gold200); border-radius: 4px;"></div>
      </div>

      <div style="text-align: center;">
        <a
          href="https://app.thefield.org/home/donation/general/632877/0"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          style="display: inline-block; padding: 0.875rem 2rem; background: var(--color-ot-gold200); color: var(--color-ot-dark); font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; transition: all 0.2s ease;">
          Support the Mission
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- What We Need Support For -->
    <h2 class="artwork-subtitle">
      What We Need Support For
    </h2>

    <p class="artwork-text">
      To complete this historic mission and maximize its impact, we need support for four critical components:
    </p>

    <div style="display: grid; gap: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 48px; padding-left: 1.5rem;">
      <p class="artwork-text" style="margin: 0;">
        · <strong>ISRO Launch Costs:</strong> $32,000
      </p>
      <p class="artwork-text" style="margin: 0;">
        · <strong>Artist Journey to India:</strong> $6,000
      </p>
      <p class="artwork-text" style="margin: 0;">
        · <strong>Educational Program:</strong> $46,000
      </p>
      <p class="artwork-text" style="margin: 0;">
        · <strong>Documentary Production:</strong> $136,000
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- The Decade Ahead -->
    <h2 class="artwork-subtitle">
      The Decade Ahead
    </h2>

    <p class="artwork-text">
      This mission doesn't end on November 28, 2025—it's just beginning.
    </p>

    <p class="artwork-text">
      For the next <strong>10 years</strong>, this satellite will orbit Earth, responding to names sent from every corner of the planet. The educational program will train <strong>thousands of teenagers</strong> in satellite technology, breaking the Space Gap for the Global South. The documentary will reach <strong>millions</strong> worldwide, sparking conversations about belonging, memory, and the sacred.
    </p>

    <p class="artwork-text">
      Orbital Temple is partnering with <strong>Sathi Roy</strong> and <strong>The Roy Foundation</strong> to make this decade-long vision culturally significant. The Roy Foundation is a nonprofit dedicated to expanding access to spiritual education, emotional healing, and consciousness tools for underserved communities worldwide—bridging ancient wisdom and modern technology to create a more conscious, connected, and compassionate world. Together, we're building the infrastructure to ensure Orbital Temple becomes a lasting movement that reaches communities across the globe.
    </p>

    <p class="artwork-text artwork-text--section-end">
      Your support doesn't just fund a launch—it creates a movement that will echo for a decade and inspire the next generation of space artists and engineers.
    </p>

    <!-- Individual Supporter Tiers -->
    <h2 class="artwork-subtitle">
      Individual Supporters
    </h2>

    <p class="artwork-text" style="margin-bottom: 32px;">
      Join the mission at a level that works for you. Individual supporters are the foundation of this historic project.
    </p>

    <div style="display: grid; gap: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 4rem; max-width: 900px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">

      <!-- $1,000 Tier -->
      <div style="background: rgba(250, 212, 58, 0.02); padding: 1.75rem; border-left: 3px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); border-radius: 4px;">
        <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1rem;">
          <h3 class="section-subtitle" style="margin: 0;">Orbital Friend</h3>
          <p style="font-size: var(--text-body-std); font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-ot-gold200); margin: 0;">$1,000</p>
        </div>
        <p class="artwork-text artwork-text--secondary" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">
          You receive: Name on website honor roll · Personalized orbital certificate when satellite launches · Documentary thank you credit · Tax-deductible receipt
        </p>
        <div style="margin-top: 1.25rem; text-align: right;">
          <a
            href="https://app.thefield.org/home/donation/general/632877/0"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            style="display: inline-block; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; font-size: 0.9rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); color: var(--color-ot-light); text-decoration: none; border-radius: 3px; transition: all 0.2s ease;">
            Make Tax-Deductible Donation
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- $2,500 Tier -->
      <div style="background: rgba(250, 212, 58, 0.02); padding: 1.75rem; border-left: 3px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); border-radius: 4px;">
        <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1rem;">
          <h3 class="section-subtitle" style="margin: 0;">Satellite Supporter</h3>
          <p style="font-size: var(--text-body-std); font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-ot-gold200); margin: 0;">$2,500</p>
        </div>
        <p class="artwork-text artwork-text--secondary" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">
          You receive: All Orbital Friend benefits · Exclusive satellite tracking app access · Artist thank you video message · Launch event livestream invitation · Tax-deductible receipt
        </p>
        <div style="margin-top: 1.25rem; text-align: right;">
          <a
            href="https://app.thefield.org/home/donation/general/632877/0"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            style="display: inline-block; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; font-size: 0.9rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); color: var(--color-ot-light); text-decoration: none; border-radius: 3px; transition: all 0.2s ease;">
            Make Tax-Deductible Donation
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- $5,000 Tier -->
      <div style="background: rgba(250, 212, 58, 0.02); padding: 1.75rem; border-left: 3px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); border-radius: 4px;">
        <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1rem;">
          <h3 class="section-subtitle" style="margin: 0;">Space Advocate</h3>
          <p style="font-size: var(--text-body-std); font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-ot-gold200); margin: 0;">$5,000</p>
        </div>
        <p class="artwork-text artwork-text--secondary" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">
          You receive: All Satellite Supporter benefits · Printed name in documentary credits · Invitation to private documentary screening · Quarterly updates from the team · Tax-deductible receipt
        </p>
        <div style="margin-top: 1.25rem; text-align: right;">
          <a
            href="https://app.thefield.org/home/donation/general/632877/0"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            style="display: inline-block; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; font-size: 0.9rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); color: var(--color-ot-light); text-decoration: none; border-radius: 3px; transition: all 0.2s ease;">
            Make Tax-Deductible Donation
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Funding Opportunities -->
    <h2 class="artwork-subtitle">
      Fund a Specific Component
    </h2>

    <p class="artwork-text" style="margin-bottom: 32px;">
      Your contribution directly funds specific aspects of the mission. Choose what speaks to you—or combine multiple to create a larger impact.
    </p>

    <div style="display: grid; gap: 2rem; margin-bottom: 4rem;">

      <!-- Satellite Launch -->
      <div style="background: rgba(250, 212, 58, 0.03); padding: 2rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); border-radius: 4px;">
        <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; margin-bottom: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1rem;">
          <h3 class="section-subtitle" style="margin: 0;">Fund the Space Launch</h3>
          <p style="font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-ot-gold200); margin: 0;">$32,000</p>
        </div>
        <p class="artwork-text">
          The actual launch cost aboard the <strong>ISRO</strong> rocket on <strong>November 28, 2025</strong>. This sends the first purely artistic satellite from the Global South into orbit, where it will remain for a decade as a temple in the sky.
        </p>
        <p class="artwork-text artwork-text--secondary" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
          You receive: "Launch Sponsor" title · Featured in all press releases · On-screen documentary acknowledgment · VIP access to launch events · Join quarterly video calls with Edson and the mission team · Certificate with satellite orbital data · Tax-deductible receipt
        </p>
        <div style="margin-top: 1.5rem; text-align: right;">
          <a
            href="https://app.thefield.org/home/donation/general/632877/0"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            style="display: inline-block; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; font-size: 0.9rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); color: var(--color-ot-light); text-decoration: none; border-radius: 3px; transition: all 0.2s ease;">
            Make Tax-Deductible Donation
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Artist Travel -->
      <div style="background: rgba(250, 212, 58, 0.03); padding: 2rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); border-radius: 4px;">
        <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; margin-bottom: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1rem;">
          <h3 class="section-subtitle" style="margin: 0;">Fund the Artist's Journey to India</h3>
          <p style="font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-ot-gold200); margin: 0;">$6,000</p>
        </div>
        <p class="artwork-text">
          Travel, accommodation, and production costs for artist Edson Pavoni and core team to witness the launch in <strong>India on November 28, 2025</strong>. This trip is essential for documentary filming, media coverage, and representing the Global South at this historic moment.
        </p>
        <p class="artwork-text artwork-text--secondary" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
          You receive: Personal thank you from artist · Behind-the-scenes documentary access · Name in documentary credits · Launch event invitation · Tax-deductible receipt
        </p>
        <div style="margin-top: 1.5rem; text-align: right;">
          <a
            href="https://app.thefield.org/home/donation/general/632877/0"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            style="display: inline-block; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; font-size: 0.9rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); color: var(--color-ot-light); text-decoration: none; border-radius: 3px; transition: all 0.2s ease;">
            Make Tax-Deductible Donation
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Educational Program -->
      <div style="background: rgba(250, 212, 58, 0.03); padding: 2rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); border-radius: 4px;">
        <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; margin-bottom: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1rem;">
          <h3 class="section-subtitle" style="margin: 0;">Fund the Educational Program</h3>
          <p style="font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-ot-gold200); margin: 0;">$46,000</p>
        </div>
        <p class="artwork-text">
          Develop and launch the complete multilingual course teaching Global South teenagers how to build satellites. Includes curriculum development, video production, platform hosting, and the first year of scholarships for underserved students. Creates lasting infrastructure for space education.
        </p>
        <p class="artwork-text artwork-text--secondary" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
          You receive: "Education Founding Sponsor" recognition · Scholarships in your name · Featured in educational materials · Meet the first cohort of students your scholarship funded (virtual or in-person) · Documentary feature segment · Speaking opportunity at launch events · Tax-deductible receipt
        </p>
        <div style="margin-top: 1.5rem; text-align: right;">
          <a
            href="https://app.thefield.org/home/donation/general/632877/0"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            style="display: inline-block; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; font-size: 0.9rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); color: var(--color-ot-light); text-decoration: none; border-radius: 3px; transition: all 0.2s ease;">
            Make Tax-Deductible Donation
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Documentary -->
      <div style="background: rgba(250, 212, 58, 0.03); padding: 2rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); border-radius: 4px;">
        <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; margin-bottom: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1rem;">
          <h3 class="section-subtitle" style="margin: 0;">Fund the Documentary Production</h3>
          <p style="font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-ot-gold200); margin: 0;">$136,000</p>
        </div>
        <p class="artwork-text">
          Complete production and post-production of <strong>"What Makes a Temple?"</strong> — the feature documentary exploring the intersection of art, technology, and the sacred. Includes filming in multiple countries, interviews with thought leaders, and premiere screenings in <strong>India</strong> and <strong>NYC</strong>.
        </p>
        <p class="artwork-text artwork-text--secondary" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
          You receive: Executive Producer credit · Featured in opening credits · Private screening for your guests · World premiere invitations (both cities) · Private dinner with Edson and documentary director before premiere · Behind-the-scenes access · Tax-deductible receipt
        </p>
        <div style="margin-top: 1.5rem; text-align: right;">
          <a
            href="https://app.thefield.org/home/donation/general/632877/0"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            style="display: inline-block; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; font-size: 0.9rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); color: var(--color-ot-light); text-decoration: none; border-radius: 3px; transition: all 0.2s ease;">
            Make Tax-Deductible Donation
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Art Collector -->
      <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(250, 212, 58, 0.12) 0%, rgba(250, 212, 58, 0.03) 100%); padding: 3rem; border: 3px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); border-radius: 4px;">
        <h3 style="font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0; color: var(--color-ot-gold200);">Become the Only Orbital Temple Art Collector</h3>

        <figure style="margin: 0 0 2rem 0;">
          <img
            src="/press/edson-pavoni-orbital-temple-clara-marques-07.webp"
            alt="Orbital Temple installation at Mercosul Biennial"
            style="width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; border-radius: 4px;"
          />
          <figcaption style="font-size: var(--text-body-sm); line-height: var(--text-body-sm-lh); color: var(--color-ot-light); opacity: 0.6; margin-top: 8px; text-align: right;">
            Orbital Temple at the 13th Mercosul Biennial, Porto Alegre. Photo by Clara Marques.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <p class="artwork-text">
          Three identical satellites were built for this mission. <strong>One</strong> launched to space on November 28, 2025. <strong>One</strong> travels to museum exhibitions worldwide. <strong>One</strong> is reserved for a generous collector who wants to fund this vision and own a piece of space art history.
        </p>

        <p class="artwork-text">
          This is not a replica—it is one of the three original satellites. A fully <strong>functional spacecraft</strong> that is also a <strong>sculpture</strong>. The satellite measures <strong>5cm³</strong> and weighs <strong>245g</strong>, with a dome made of <strong>gold</strong>. This is a <strong>1/1 artwork</strong>. No one else will ever have this piece.
        </p>

        <p class="artwork-text">
          As the collector, you will receive the same installation created for the <strong>13th Mercosul Biennial</strong>—a complete museological display that showcases the satellite as both art and technology. This installation has been exhibited at major international venues and represents the highest standard of space art presentation.
        </p>

        <p class="artwork-text" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          Your support funds the entire vision—the launch, the educational program, and the documentary that will spark global conversations about the sacred in the age of space exploration. Your name becomes permanently intertwined with this historic mission.
        </p>

        <div style="margin-top: 2rem; text-align: center;">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-ot-gold200); margin: 0 0 1rem 0;">$50,000</p>
          <a
            href="mailto:edson@spacesandcreatures.com?subject=Orbital Temple Art Collector Inquiry"
            style="display: inline-block; padding: 1rem 2.5rem; background: var(--color-ot-gold200); color: var(--color-ot-dark); font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.1rem; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; transition: all 0.2s ease;">
            Inquire About This Opportunity
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Current Supporters -->
    <h2 class="artwork-subtitle">
      With Gratitude to Our Supporters
    </h2>

    <p class="artwork-text" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
      Orbital Temple is made possible by institutions, individuals, and believers in radical inclusion who understand that art creates tomorrow's imaginaries.
    </p>

    <div style="margin: 0 0 3rem 0; padding: 2.5rem; background: rgba(250, 212, 58, 0.05); border: 2px solid var(--color-ot-gold200); border-radius: 4px;">
      <img
        src="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/5f467eca8efd267ebe6dc293/63b59b7475377c988b04eb2e_Pearmill-logo-svg.svg"
        alt="Pearmill"
        style="height: 40px; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;"
      />
      <p class="artwork-text" style="margin: 0 0 1rem 0; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ot-gold200);">
        Founding Supporter
      </p>
      <p class="artwork-text" style="margin: 0; line-height: 1.6;">
        Pearmill is one of the fastest-growing performance marketing agencies in the US—a group of designers, marketers, and engineers working together to help grow some of the most iconic startups in the world. Their generous support enabled the Orbital Temple team to purchase critical components and develop the open-source hardware that makes this satellite mission possible.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="artwork-text" style="text-align: center; font-style: italic; opacity: 0.9;">
      Your name could be here. Join us in creating history.
    </p>

    <!-- The Team -->
    <h2 class="artwork-subtitle">
      The People Behind This Mission
    </h2>

    <p class="artwork-text" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
      Orbital Temple is a 10-year commitment. It's led by two people who have spent their lives bridging art, technology, and human connection—and who are building the infrastructure to sustain this vision for the decade ahead.
    </p>

    <!-- Team Grid -->
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 3rem; margin-bottom: 4rem;">

      <!-- Edson Pavoni -->
      <div>
        <img
          src="/sponsors/edson-pavoni-portrait.webp"
          alt="Edson Pavoni"
          style="width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 1; object-fit: cover; border-radius: 4px; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;"
        />
        <h3 class="section-subtitle" style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Edson Pavoni</h3>
        <p class="artwork-text" style="margin-bottom: 1rem; font-size: var(--text-body-secondary); opacity: 0.8;">
          Artist & Technologist
        </p>
        <p class="artwork-text" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
          Edson is an artist and technologist who explores human intimacy at the intersection of art and technology. His practice spans architectural installations, algorithms, AI-generated imagery, poetry, photography, and satellite technology.
        </p>
        <p class="artwork-text" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
          With over <strong>20 years</strong> of experience, he has been part of creative teams for the <strong>2016 Rio Olympics</strong> and the <strong>Inter American Development Bank</strong>. He was recognized as one of the <strong>50 most innovative Brazilian professionals</strong> by Proxxima Magazine and received two consecutive <strong>IF Design Awards</strong> in 2017 and 2018.
        </p>
        <p class="artwork-text artwork-text--secondary">
          His work has been exhibited at the 13th Mercosul Biennial (Brazil), IX International Biennale (Uzbekistan), and NTU Global Digital Art Prize (Singapore).
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Sathi Roy -->
      <div>
        <img
